AN UNCLE is believed to be in hiding after allegedly giving his two-year-old nephew alcohol! The uncle was allegedly boozing at home on Saturday when he decided to share some of his alcohol with his nephew. But things took an ugly turn when the child from Inanda, north of Durban became sick. He allegedly vomited and became unconscious. The little boy was rushed to hospital, where he is fighting for his life. But a police source said the uncle was not found at home and is suspected to be in hiding following the incident. KZN police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbele said a case of attempted murder was being investigated by Inanda cops. “A two-year-old boy was allegedly found unconscious after being given liquor by a known suspect. “The child was taken to hospital for medical attention. “No arrests have been made and investigations continue,” said Mbele.